data.text:
@_Stuart_Taylor_ @Jailender Also note that when he joined county, the squad already included the two best players that we've had in at least ten years, Boyce and Irvine. 
Without them, the wheels came off very rapidly.
@Jailender @MarcJWallace @Jailender for goodness sake lad, do not get yourself into shit over this, no matter what you might want to say. no worth it
@b0ydy09 @Jailender He’s a fan of gypsy ⚽️teams then 🤷‍♂️😂

@Jailender @DarkBlue62 @Type232 @MarcJWallace Dodds was at Dens yesterday morning then was told to go after the fans made it known they didn’t want him. Boyle helped with training. Pretty safe to say Dodds won’t be #2. 5 mins time from now “Dundee are delighted to name Billy Dodds..... haha”
@Type232 @DarkBlue62 @Jailender @MarcJWallace Agree with that. As long as he doesn’t miss training either lol.  17 year old is cutting it a bit fine tho 🙈😅
@Jailender No skeletons in my closet or Fergie's

@DarkBlue62 @Type232 @stevebarham1893 @MarcJWallace What’s the latest with regards to McIntyre wanting Dodds as his assistant?
Still an option? Or are rumours true McIntyre will walk if he can’t get Dodds?
@Jailender I didn’t think he should have been sacked at that point but seemingly, myself and others around me in the West Stand who aren’t vocal on social media are in the supposed minority.

@stevebarham1893 @DarkBlue62 @Jailender @MarcJWallace Derek McInnes was banging players wives left, right and centre but is still at Aberdeen In all fairness I don't care if McIntyre is fucking them in the centre circle at half time! As long as he wins games and gets us up the table!
@Jailender Only problem didn’t sack him sooner
@DarkBlue62 @Jailender @MarcJWallace Yeah funny heard the same in work today from a guy that works in Alness. After the Dodds fiasco boys asking for odds on him going already 🙈

@_Stuart_Taylor_ @Jailender Absolutely Stuart. Jim's tombola and humping it up from the back approach had worn dreadfully thin. Haven't met 1 County fan who was surprised at the sacking. Hiring Coyle proved to be the only mistake made.
@DannyNedeIko @Jailender Aye, come on Jailender, get it spilt

@Jailender Not many people in Scottish football would have got away with "That Photo" being uploaded to social media. Compare that to the pathetic overreaction the papers had to the Midge thing earlier this year.
